caption: Great fast-casual Chinese food. Friendly staff and located in a great area. Make sure to try their bowls and Mak wings, they are delicious. Be sure to check them out next time you are in the Wicker Park area!

I went to MAK (Modern Asian Kitchen) a few times and loved it. It's a casual, cheap and fairly healthy option on the busy Division Street in Wicker Park. We have ordered this too many times to count. Really, the only thing we've ever ordered is the MAK goji with zesty cucumbers which are essentially sweet and vinegary pickled cucumbers. ONE word: Impeccable!

This place is pretty decent. I ordered the chicken bowl, one donut, and shared some falafel and kimcheesy balls with my coworker. The kimcheesy balls are pretty small and in my opinion not super worth it. The donut and the falafel though? Both exceptional. The chicken bowl I had was average. The rice was a bit overcooked and not very warm. Will probably go back just for the falafel and donut.
Tasty!
Kimchi balls and falafel rice on point. Great taste and fast service.

MAK is our go-to date night spot or hangry spot or friends-in-town-and-we-need-an-impressive-snack spot. The wings are absolutely incredible, we get a double order every time and fight over them they’re so good. The Gogi with beef is also awesome as are the egg rolls. MAK’s team is friendly, fast, and super helpful. They have a patio to eat your carry out at during Covid and great drink specials often on wine and sake and MARS beers too. A favorite spot in Wicker Park for sure!
Great healthy options
Ordered 45 bowls for a catering. Everything about it was fantastic!
Just delicious takeout!! Quick and reliable. Recommend the broccoli chicken or the mak chicken bowl. Also, the spicy kimchee rice balls are amaze balls!
I love this place! Clean, spacious bar Strong drinks Fun games Filipino inspired menu with awesome food What more can you ask for?
Amazing staff and service! Always greeted.
Food is great and delivery is always lightning fast.

I dine in this great spot quite often! This is my favorite place to pass a nice evening.  I visit this place frequently. The food is fantastic, the staff is courteous and the prices are reasonable. I enjoy meeting in this restaurant to have a decent dinner.
My go to Place for whenever I am craving Noodles. The Pad Se Ew and Drunken noodles are my favorite, but the Joom Noodle is also good.

Chicken wings are the best thing I have had on the menu. Delicious And excellent value. We get them often and have not been disappointed. Sweet with a kick. They hit the spot when looking for meaty and flavorable korean style chicken wings that won't break the bank.
Great food and good shrimp
Bibimbop was delicious!

Food is average. We got Pad Thai with beef, & a pork bowl. The Kimcheesy Ball was above average, very good. The bathroom had no soap, which frankly makes one hope they use the other bathroom for the cook. There’s no hot water because? I suppose their thinking is no need to get your hands really clean. Anyhow, it’s OK. I’d come back if I lived in the area. But I don’t so I’ll move on to find something more creative. Prices are reasonable.
One of the few affordable lunch places left in this area. Can feed two easily for around $20
Try the Mak Steak with broccoli on brown rice. It's very tasty and it doesn't taste like it's high in salt.
Awesome food, very welcoming employees, always  awesome ambience. They charge affordable pricing and the food quality is excellent. Keep it up.

We had MAK delivered tonight.  I paid $4 extra to add shrimp to my noodles.  There was virtually no shrimp.  I also paid extra to get a Tazo Iced Tea instead of Lipton, but they sent Lipton anyway (and still charged the higher price)  I've also never had such a greasy egg roll or noodles from any restaurant.  It wasn't very late at night (8:30 on a Saturday) but it seemed like everything we got was pulled out of whatever was the very last from the bottom of a large fryer.
Obsessed with this place. Always so fresh and huge portions. It never fails. 🔥
Great Korean BBQ Wings! The best around.

This place is awesome. The best way to describe it is like a Chipotle-style restaurant for various Asian foods. High quality incredients and a lot of effort placed into prep and presentation. The bowls are incredible, and the portion sizes are huge. Cannot recommend enough.
Decent Asian food. Fast and good service. Nice for a grab and go meal.
Amazing family owned restaurant
Wow, this food is delicious ! I love living in walking distance to grab some Kimcheesy Riceballs!!! and of course my husband loves the Korean Friend Chicken Wangs!!

Good Day Fellow Googleplexians, (Did I just Coin that term?, Copyright/Trademark!  So, let me start out by saying I consider myself to be an Epicurean & Professor Of Gastronomy (Self Crowned), & a self-made Chef (Honorary, & again gave myself that title) But, In a fat Chicagoan & a foodie that not only has mad skills in the kitchen, but have worn every hat in the restaurant industry you can think of. Simply, I'm not snooty, easy to please, & good food is just good food.  Which brings me to 'MAK'.  Haven't had Chinese food in a while, and I love all the unique, Oriental flavors of Asiana, so a new place, representing such, I was excited.  I purchased my mandatory pork egg rolls, & one of their 'special' dishes with rice noodles & paid $4 to upgrade: add beef.  I call the order in, directing to give me the wide rice noodles, & fry them crispy.  I arrive for pick up, my order hasn't even been started. The guy goes over to a steam table, grabs 2 tiny sad looking soggy ore-made egg rolls, takes a plastic container, slaps 2 scoops of Pre-made slop and goes to put lid on, (oh, the beef!) then tings some little nibblets if Beef, throws on too gives it to me.  There's a line, so I let the crispy noodle request go, & figured I'd try first time as is.  And my assessment: 1) Called in pick-up, get there, not even started.(not busy) 2) egg rolls tiny, soggy, Pre-made warm and must be pork 'flavored' cause there wasn't no pig meat in there. 3) 2 scoops of soggy slip, %90 noodle & cabbage (that's being liberal, prob less) 4) Noodles not cooked crispy as requested 5) Paid $4 for beef that was warm, dry, flavorless, overcooked, and you'd get more beef out of a small Slim Jim Just disgusting, might as well have set money on fire, cause after I committed to finish the egg rolls, a few bites of bland noodles & I threw it out. Not even worth the calories. I seriously would have been happier & more satisfied w/ an apple for dinner, or a 3 minute Ramen Noodle at home.. at least it would have been hot, have flavor, and cost pennies instead of $20. Ruined my taste for Chinese food for a while. Honestly, I feel robbed, it was gross.  I'm not being a jerk or exaggerating nor trying to be mean. I'm simply stating my experience & the facts as they are, And if this helps the chefs or the owners, managers or cooks,  Or saves somebody else from horrible food way overpriced and wasting their time and money then that is what it is.  Most disappointing me all I can think of in a very long time especially for when I paid for.  I really don’t know if people order to have a 3, 4 or 5 star review for this place,  But it’s hard to believe. And I’m easy to please I love Chinese food Cantonese Japanese Vietnamese Korean and Filipino all the orient flavor but it’s hard to believe. And I’m easy to please love Chinese food Cantonese Japanese Vietnamese Korean and Filipino all the Flavors if the Orient, But no I don’t see me giving this a second try.

Super affordable, fast, and DELICIOUS. The gluten free General Tsos keeps me coming back. We are not from Chicago but now I must come to MAK every time we are in town. I love that you can pick how spicy you want your dish.
Great food and good portions.

Have been coming here for the past four years and it is one if the better quick serves around. Food is tasty and priced well. Really wanted to rate it 5 stars but just can't. The only reason for 3 stars is that there is absolutely no consistency anymore. One day the food is very overcooked to where you can't chew it while the next it is perfect. That isn't enough to stop me from going but very disappointing that you never know which you will get.

We were surprised how good the stir fried was. The MAK Beef and wings on extra spicy are the my favorites. Very friendly staff. Just a little on the expensive side; Our bill is around $87 for one appetizer, two entrees and two drinks with tips.

Mak might be my favorite quick lunch place in the neighborhood. Each meal you can tell the food is freshly made and of good quality. I really enjoy the bowls and chicken wings. Never had a bad interaction with any of the employees and their patio in the summer is always well shaded and welcoming.

An interesting Asian fusion fast food. The place is small, only 7 tables to seat in. However, service is very friendly and the food is good. A lot of people order to out from this place. I tried the chicken lolipops and general tsao bowl, they were good. I would recommend this place for some good Asian fixed.
The food wasn't bad but nothing amazing it didn't wow me. The pad Thai was too saucy, not enough dynamic flavors and the egg rolls were flavorless. I was hoping for a more authentic pad thai.
I have only had the food through postmates delivery and it's great! Very tasty with complex flavors. We order almost once a week since we discovered them. Yum!

My company catered from them. Really interested fusion bowl! Super super flavorful. Mine had chicken breast, brown rice, greens, pickled carrots, corn succatash, trio herb mix, roasted garlic. I loved it!

Great spot for quick Asian food. They have some unique takes on Asian dishes, and their bulgogi and kimchi is great!

Fast casual asian cuisine. Good spot to stop and grab a quick lunch or get delivered.  The MAK donuts are also a good little treat.  The restaurant itself has booths and outlets, so if you want to post up and do a little bit of work with lunch, definitely possible.

TLDR: inexpensive and tasty. Food = 4 star, The service = 6 stars  The staff and service is top notch. I’m not sure what I was expecting but the folks here went above and beyond. The girl behind the counter was especially helpful. Everything was good, but I will be back specifically because the employees are great.  The food is what you expect. Bowls, soups, wraps etc etc. it’s very very good for the price and it comes out fairly fast.  The environment is nice. It’s small, cozy and very chill.  The chork thing is a little weird, I think I would prefer just basic chopsticks.

Food done on the go, fresh, relatively fast . staff is friendly, food is served in sturdy containers, and in nice complimentary bags....ya Rham! Simple, customer friendly menu. Place is decorated nicely so you can dine in. Nice fork/chop stick design.

The food was delicious, decor is nice but the experience is cafeteria-like despite the prices.  I went in with my daughters for dinner. We ordered and I was asked if I wanted to add a tip which I did given we were eating there. However, all you get for your tip is the food brought to the table.  They never cleared the empty dishes, we had to bring them to the counter ourselves. We then bought another round of sake. They never came to wipe the table or clear any remaining dishes.  There were five or six people working and they were eating, texting, cleaning and NO ONE ever came to our table. Maybe I am missing what this dining experience is supposed to be like, but it appears not to be anyone's job to make it a good one.

Got fried rice and there was some sort of hard plastic or glass in it. It chipped my front tooth. Will definitely never eat from here again. Off to the dentist.

Pad Thai is one of my favorite dishes... have eaten it a lot.  MAK Restaurant serves one of WORST dishes in all my experience... very rubbery, little or no spices other than the hot pepper to make it spicey.  Don't eat here.

The food here is excellent! The menu is extensive and has something for everyone, but it can be complex & overwhelming if you have never been here before. We navigated the menu with the help of the guy at the registered and ordered the bowls. I had the beef with broccoli & Rice - the portion was large and the meet was tender.  It was all delicious! everything was fresh, and the service was excellent.  When our meal was done the owner came over to make sure everything was OK. We'll definitely be back.

Big fan of MAK. Happy to find good quality Asian food nearby that we can eat in or take-out. Love that the food is fresh and not bogged down with salty sauces. I enjoy the quinoa option if I don't want rice, very fresh veggies, the chicken wangs are amazing, and you can wash it down with a nice cold beer. Also, the meat served is high quality without all of the msg, hormones, etc.. that you find at other Asian restaurants throughout the city. Good food, friendly staff, sustainable & clean, good prices, and of course really delicious food.

I'm rarely in this neighborhood, at least during the hours that decent people are awake and this place would be open, but the one time I went courtesy of an incentive I really liked it. Our food was really fresh and delicious, but the portions seemed small. That could have just been my hunger talking so I've have to evaluate that again on my next visit. I also remember the extras ingredients costing a bit extra but I'm assuming they are locally sourced or something
Everything was Great! From the Customer service to the Food!! Awesome Spot! I recommended MAK to Everyone!!!
Fire. Plan and simple. I ate it so fast because it was so good I am not even sure if I ate it.

I think this is a gem. you get a downtown experience for a reasonable price. The sushi was delicious and you are able to substitute the white rice for brown on your sushi roll. The green tea ice cream was also really good. Cannot remember exactly what I had for an entree I just remember it being spicy and extremely tasty.
Loved the food. Reminds me of the Asian food version of Chipotle. The service was great. Will be back if I am in the area

MAK tries and they score some points for the effort.  I feel like the goal was to be a pan Asian chipotle style restaurant.  Fresh organic ingredients cooked up to order.  The menu is pretty straightforward and you can make healthier choices or not so healthy choices (meaning you can have deep fried things).  The concentration is on fresh organic ingredients.  The staff is pretty friendly and helpful in navigating the menu.  The highlight was the chicken wings with a little help from their homemade hot sauce.  The sauce has a panda on it and that makes me laugh.  The rice bowl that I had was a mix of brown and white rice (my choice to mix the two) and was the General MAK chicken.  It was a bit on the salty side and not a far departure from the other general chicken you may be used to seeing on your favorite take out joint (you know... that T-so guy).  My meal was about average.  I'm a bit picky when it comes to my Asian food and I won't expect to find my next Asian meal in Wicker Park.

This place reminds me of a Chipotle. Except it's an Asian-Chipotle. And you order what you want from the register, but then you can see them make it in front of you, if you please. Otherwise, you can have a seat and they'll bring it to your table. I tried the Spicy Chicken, which was crispy and juicy, but a bit salty. There were 2 kinds of homemade hot sauce, but they didn't have enough of a kick to satisfy my spicy level.  The employees in here were super nice. They made awesome recommendations, and made sure we were 100% good.  The best thing about this place is the Chork-Chopstick Fork! You can use the utensil like a fork, or you can break the plastic in half and use it as a pair of chopsticks. INGENIOUS!  Also, try their donuts. They have small 5-spice flavor for $1! YUM!!

Finally an Asian place that uses sustainable ingredients! Their format is kinda like chipotle, but they're a small operation. I don't typically order beef entrees from Chinese places, but their mak beef bowl w a side of mushrooms is pretty much the most delicious thing ever. Plus they give you a 'chork' to eat your meal, that looks like a cross between a fork and chopsticks. I need a whole set of chorks!!

Although it is a little over-priced, I like having a higher-quality 'fast food'-esque Asian spot in Wicker Park.  Almost everything I've tried there has been pretty good, so it is tough to go wrong if you are headed there for the first time.  I'm hopeful this place will stay in the neighborhood for years to come.
The prices are a little high for what you get, have to add on vegetables and what not for extra cost.  Food is good, not many traditional chinese options such as egg rolls.

Food is great, decor is bad.  It looks like it should be Chipotle and cheap and sort of manufactured/corporate, but it's actually local and the owner is always around.  Love the brocolli and the proteins are all good.  So it's strangely pricey, but just think of it as dinner + leftovers for lunch and it's worth it.

Man, I love Tommy Wang's new spot. He does it right. Such a gentleman too. I really can't say enough good things about him and his restaurant, but I particularly like the emphasis on healthfully grown meats and veggies. Definitely go! This is the type of place and entrepreneur that deserves you giving it & him a shot. Very reasonably priced too!

Awesome spot for asian food.  Theres a patio outside and a row of booths inside to sit down, with an open kitchen next to the registers.  Soups were brought in plastic bowls and the owner brought us bowls with our food.  I had the pork bowl with white rice.  Just the right portions.  Grabbed a fountain drink and enjoyed my meal listening to some really good music (unusual nowadays) at a low enough level to enjoy while still holding a conversation.  Not sure why so many places get that but a pleasure when they get it right.  Definitely coming back.
